            <title>[LUCENE-2225] TestPerfTasksLogic.testBGSearchTaskThreads sometimes runs forever</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2225</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This appears to happen because hudson is very started, so, threads get scheduled in &quot;interesting&quot; ways.  It&apos;s actually a good test case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12445806">LUCENE-2225</key>
            <summary>TestPerfTasksLogic.testBGSearchTaskThreads sometimes runs forever</summary>
